TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bertrand, Marianne
AU  - Kramarz, Francis
T1  - Does Entry Regulation Hinder Job Creation? Evidence from the French Retail Industry*
PY  - 2002
Y1  - 2002/11/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355302320935052
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 117
IS  - 4
SP  - 1369
EP  - 1413
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Are product market and entry regulation key sources of low employment growth in many European countries? We investigate this question in the context of the French retail trade industry. Since 1974, approval by regional zoning boards has been required for the creation or extension of any large retain store in France. We exploit a unique database that provides time- and region-specific variation in boards' approval decisions. We show that stronger deterrence of entry by the boards increased retailer concentration and slowed down employment growth in France.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355302320935052
ER  - 



